TRUST DEED AND MORTGAGE
Borrower: Whitmore Properties LLC
Lender: Sovereign National Bank
Principal Amount: $3,200,000
Property: 87 Cedar Avenue, Commercial Parcel ID: 09-8874-A

Covenants of the Borrower
Until the Principal and accrued interest are paid in full, the Borrower covenants and agrees:
a) To maintain comprehensive all-risk property insurance in an amount not less than the full replacement value of the improvements, with loss payable to Lender as mortgagee;
b) To pay all taxes, assessments, and governmental charges levied against the Property before they become delinquent;
c) Not to permit any material alteration, demolition, or removal of any improvements on the Property without Lender's prior written consent;
d) To allow Lender or its agents to enter upon the Property at any reasonable time for the purpose of inspection;
e) Upon the occurrence of a Transfer of an interest in the Property without Lender's consent, including but not limited to a sale, lease of three years or more, or a change in majority control of Borrower if Borrower is a legal entity, Lender may, at its option, accelerate the maturity and declare the entire unpaid Principal and accrued interest immediately due and payable. This provision is commonly known as a "Due-on-Sale" clause.
